  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "We merged the two splits, and randomly sampled 100 utterances for testing, which left us with 784 utterances for training.",
    "For test data sampling, we used the train_test_split method from the datasets foot_2 library (Lhoest et al., 2021), setting the random seed option to zero.",
    "The ACL 60/60 dataset was required for \"constrained\" submissions to the IWSLT's \"Model Compression\" track.",
    "After layer pruning of the Qwen2-Audio-7B-Instruct model (cf.",
    "Section 3), we needed to use more training data to restore the translation quality of the unpruned model."
  ],
